# Executive Intelligence Engine: v3.3 Full Audit & v3.4 Copilot Instruction

## v3.3 Verdict: Significant Progress — Two Issues Remain

The v3.3 run shows real improvements. Past jobs fill rate jumped from near-zero to **38% (PJ1) and 24% (PJ2)**. BCBST CMO is now correctly Robin Young (not Henry Smith). BCBSLA CMO Brian Keller is still in the slot but his past jobs now correctly show he was previously the BCBSLA SVP & CMO — so the BD team can see the context. UHC Chief Medical is now Rhonda Randall (not Sam Ho). All v3.2 wins held.

However, there are two issues to fix:

**Issue 1 — BD Notes are identical for all 5 rows of every payer (confirmed by data analysis)**
The audit script confirmed that all 10 payers have the exact same note repeated 5 times. The BD Note is written at the payer level and then stamped onto every row. It needs to be written at the **executive level** — each row should contain a note specific to that individual (their tenure, background, engagement hook, and any departure/transition signal), not a copy of the payer-level summary.

**Issue 2 — BCBSLA CMO slot still has Brian Keller (Chief Growth Officer)**
The v3.3 title-tightening fix did not take effect for Brian Keller. His title "Chief Growth Officer" should have been rejected by the CMO persona filter. The slot should be empty (—) unless a true CMO exists.

**Issue 3 — IBX Chief Medical is empty (Dr. Rodrigo Cerdá disappeared)**
Dr. Rodrigo Cerdá was correctly identified in v3.2 as IBX's Chief Medical Officer. He is gone in v3.3 — this is an LLM nondeterminism regression. The fix is to add a confidence-based retry: if the Chief Medical slot is empty for a large payer (IBX, UHC, BCBS plans), run a targeted search for "[payer name] Chief Medical Officer" before giving up.

