### Fix 2 — Harden CMO Title Rejection (crew.py)

The v3.3 fix did not prevent Brian Keller (Chief Growth Officer) from appearing in the BCBSLA CMO slot. The title rejection needs to be enforced at the **Python level**, not just in the LLM prompt.

After the LLM returns its classification, add a Python-level post-processor that checks the title of each classified executive against a hard rejection list for each persona:

```python
_PERSONA_TITLE_REJECT = {
    "CMO": frozenset({
        "growth officer", "revenue officer", "commercial officer",
        "strategy officer", "operating officer", "operations officer",
        "financial officer", "legal officer", "compliance officer",
    }),
    "VP Experience": frozenset({
        "quality", "population health", "clinical", "finance",
        "strategy", "growth", "revenue", "legal", "compliance",
        "operations", "supply chain",
    }),
}

def _title_passes_persona_filter(persona: str, title: str) -> bool:
    """Return False if the title contains a rejection keyword for this persona."""
    title_lc = (title or "").lower()
    reject_terms = _PERSONA_TITLE_REJECT.get(persona, frozenset())
    return not any(term in title_lc for term in reject_terms)
```

Call this function in the post-LLM validation loop, after the employer-match check and before the deceased check:

